================================================================================
Third-party component: Glocal-IB (vendored, modified)
================================================================================

Directory:   GlocalIB/
Upstream:     "Glocal Information Bottleneck for Time Series Imputation"
              Jie Yang, Kexin Zhang, Guibin Zhang, Philip S. Yu, Kaize Ding.
              NeurIPS 2025. arXiv:2510.04910.
License:      MIT (see GlocalIB/LICENSE)

The code in GlocalIB/ is a vendored copy of the Glocal-IB / SAITS imputation
model, derived from the fork github.com/bmattivi03/GlocalIB_Improvements. It has
been modified by the project team with the following additions, integrated into
the upstream model.py / core.py:

  - mod_e: a Variational Information Bottleneck (VIB) regulariser, active at
    training time.
  - mod_p: a Self-Supervised Held-out Blend (SSHB), active at inference time.
  - physical_loss.py and the core.py auxiliary-loss hook: post-hoc physical
    constraints for the energy-market panel.

All upstream copyright and the MIT terms in GlocalIB/LICENSE are retained. If
you use the imputation model in academic work, please cite the original paper
(see CITATION.cff and GlocalIB/README.md).
